{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bf5105c5-3d97-49dc-824f-e47e78fb5e1d","content":"Since MSTest.Sdk **3.x** already defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform, the migration is straightforward:\n\n### In your `.csproj` / `Directory.Build.props`\n\n**Remove** (or set to `false`) the `UseVSTest` property:\n\n```diff\n  <Sdk Name=\"MSTest.Sdk\" Version=\"3.8.0\" />\n  <PropertyGroup>\n-   <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nThat's the only required change — MSTest.Sdk will wire up Microsoft.Testing.Platform automatically.\n\n### What else to be aware of\n\n| Area | Notes |\n|---|---|\n| **`dotnet test`** | Still works — the SDK bridges it to the new platform. |\n| **`.runsettings`** | Still supported, but platform-specific options now use `--` CLI syntax (e.g. `--filter`). |\n| **CLI** | The built test binary is now directly runnable: `./YourTests --list-tests`, `./YourTests --filter \"Name=Foo\"`. |\n| **CI / code coverage** | If you pass `-- RunConfiguration.CollectSourceInformation=true` or similar VSTest args, verify they still apply; some become no-ops. |\n\nNo extra NuGet packages are needed — `MSTest.Sdk` bundles everything.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9a42fe54-a531-4701-8135-9aa9b1a0a671","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The working directory is empty and doesn't have any relevant files. This is a general knowledge question about MSTest migration. Let me answer based on my knowledge.\n\nWith MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0, when you have `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>`, you're using the legacy VSTest runner. To switch to Microsoft.Testing.Platform, here's what needs to change:\n\n1. Remove `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` (or set it to `false`) from your project file. MSTest.Sdk 3.x defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform when `UseVSTest` is not set to true.\n\n\n2. The test execution will still work with `dotnet test`, but you can also run the test executable directly since it's now using the new platform runner.\n3. Any VSTest-specific configurations like `.runsettings` files may require adjustments to work with the new runner.","outputTokens":576,"requestId":"042C:D1352:1DDEC11:21B0610:69E81A52"},"id":"5f7f0354-81d0-436d-89f5-1d94c54f944a","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:46:24.669Z","parentId":"70bd4140-93fa-4bc6-91b0-93d776df5093"}
